# {{STACK_NAME}} implementation rules

Applies to **{{STACK_ROLE}}** work in this repository.

## Read this when
- A task touches {{STACK_NAME}} files or libraries
- You are debugging framework behavior, introducing a new dependency, or changing architecture
- You are writing or reviewing bug fixes that should teach the team something durable

## Core boundaries
- Start with the boring, built-in path before inventing abstractions.
- For reproducible bugs: prove the bug with a failing test or equivalent evidence before fixing it.
- Stop brute forcing after repeated failed attempts without new evidence — research the docs and existing code first.
- Prefer the narrowest durable prevention: tests/lints/harness before comments.

## Project-specific rules to curate
